- Add personality and craft
- Make the page feel alive

## Implementation Details

### Option 1: CSS-Only (Simpler)

```css
.hero-title .typed-text {
  display: inline-block;
  overflow: hidden;
  white-space: nowrap;
  border-right: none; /* Cursor handled separately */
  animation: typing 2s steps(35) forwards;
  width: 0;
}

.hero-title .typed-text.typed-complete {
  width: 100%;
}

@keyframes typing {
  from { width: 0; }
  to { width: 100%; }
}

/* Cursor blink (already exists, may need adjustment) */
.hero-title .cursor {
  animation: blink 1s step-end infinite;
}

@keyframes blink {
  50% { opacity: 0; }
}

/* Reduced motion: show immediately */
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .hero-title .typed-text {
    animation: none;
    width: 100%;
  }
}
```

### Option 2: JavaScript (More Control)

```javascript
// assets/js/main.js
function typeWriter(element, text, speed = 50) {
  if (window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches) {
    element.textContent = text;
    return;
  }

  let i = 0;
  element.textContent = '';

  function type() {
    if (i < text.length) {
      element.textContent += text.charAt(i);
      i++;
      setTimeout(type, speed);
    }
  }

  // Start after a brief delay
  setTimeout(type, 500);
}

// Initialize on page load
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
  const heroTitle = document.querySelector('.hero-title .typed-text');
  if (heroTitle) {
    const text = heroTitle.dataset.text || heroTitle.textContent;
    typeWriter(heroTitle, text, 60);
  }
});
```

### HTML with JavaScript Approach

```html
<h1 class="hero-title">
  <span class="typed-text" data-text="DevOps Technical Lead & Consultant"></span>
  <span class="cursor">_</span>
</h1>
```

### Timing Considerations

- Type speed: ~50-70ms per character
- Total animation: ~2-2.5 seconds
- Start delay: 300-500ms (after page loads)
- Only run once per visit (don't replay on navigation)

### Session Storage (Optional)

To prevent replay on navigation:
```javascript
if (!sessionStorage.getItem('heroTyped')) {
  typeWriter(heroTitle, text);
  sessionStorage.setItem('heroTyped', 'true');
} else {
  heroTitle.textContent = text;
}
```

