## Overview

Transform the sticky header into a glass-morphism effect—semi-transparent background with backdrop blur. This creates a premium, layered feel where content scrolls "behind" the header.

## Background

Glass-morphism (popularized by Apple's Big Sur, used by Linear, Vercel) creates:
- Depth through transparency and blur
- Visual continuity as content scrolls
- Premium, modern appearance
- Clear separation of navigation from content

## Implementation Details

### CSS for Glass Header

```css
.site-header {
  background: rgba(22, 27, 34, 0.8); /* Semi-transparent */
  backdrop-filter: blur(12px);
  -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(12px); /* Safari */
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(48, 54, 61, 0.5);
  transition: 
    background-color 0.3s ease,
    box-shadow 0.3s ease;
}

/* Enhanced state when scrolled (more opaque, add shadow) */
