# Task: Audit and Fix Touch Targets

## Overview

Audit all interactive elements on mobile and ensure they meet the 48x48px minimum touch target size. Fix any elements that are too small.

## Background

Touch targets need to be larger than click targets:
- Fingers are less precise than cursors
- Minimum 48x48px (exceeds Apple's 44px guideline)
- Minimum 8px gap between adjacent targets
- Critical for usability and accessibility

## Implementation Details

### Elements to Audit

1. **Buttons** (.btn)
2. **Navigation links** (.page-link, .nav-link)
3. **Footer links**
4. **Any inline links in content**
5. **Social icons** (if present)
6. **Hamburger menu button** (when added)

### CSS Fixes

```css
@media (max-width: 767px) {
  /* Buttons - ensure minimum size */
  .btn {
    min-height: 48px;
    min-width: 48px;
    padding: 14px 24px;
  }

  /* Navigation links - add padding for touch area */
  .page-link, .nav-link {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    min-height: 48px;
    padding: 12px 16px;
  }

  /* Footer links */
  .site-footer a {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    min-height: 44px;
    padding: 8px 12px;
  }

  /* Ensure gap between adjacent targets */
  .site-nav {
    gap: 8px;
  }

  .hero-cta {
    gap: 12px;
  }
}
```

### Visual vs. Touch Area

Touch area can be larger than visual area:

```css
/* Visual button is compact, touch area is 48px */
.btn-icon {
  position: relative;
  width: 32px;
  height: 32px;
}

.btn-icon::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  top: 50%;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
  width: 48px;
  height: 48px;
  /* Invisible but touchable */
}
```

### Verification Script

```javascript
// Debug: highlight elements with small touch targets
document.querySelectorAll('a, button, [role="button"]').forEach(el => {
  const rect = el.getBoundingClientRect();
  if (rect.width < 48 || rect.height < 48) {
    el.style.outline = '3px solid red';
    console.warn('Small touch target:', el, rect.width, rect.height);
  }
});
```

