# Task: Create Staggered Entrance Animations

## Overview

When multiple related elements enter the viewport (like a list of services or skills), they should animate in with staggered timing—each element slightly after the previous one, creating a cascading effect.

## Background

Staggered animations:
- Create visual rhythm and flow
- Guide the eye through content sequentially
- Feel more crafted than simultaneous animation
- Reduce perceived load time (content "streams" in)

## Implementation Details

### CSS Stagger Classes

```css
/* Container that staggers children */
.stagger-children > .animate-on-scroll:nth-child(1) { --stagger-delay: 0s; }
.stagger-children > .animate-on-scroll:nth-child(2) { --stagger-delay: 0.1s; }
.stagger-children > .animate-on-scroll:nth-child(3) { --stagger-delay: 0.2s; }
.stagger-children > .animate-on-scroll:nth-child(4) { --stagger-delay: 0.3s; }
.stagger-children > .animate-on-scroll:nth-child(5) { --stagger-delay: 0.4s; }
.stagger-children > .animate-on-scroll:nth-child(6) { --stagger-delay: 0.5s; }
/* Add more as needed */

.stagger-children > .animate-on-scroll.animate-in {
  animation-delay: var(--stagger-delay, 0s);
}
```

### Alternative: JavaScript-Based Stagger

```javascript
// In main.js, modify observer callback
const staggeredContainers = document.querySelectorAll('.stagger-children');

staggeredContainers.forEach(container => {
  const children = container.querySelectorAll('.animate-on-scroll');
  children.forEach((child, index) => {
    child.style.setProperty('--stagger-delay', `${index * 0.1}s`);
  });
});
```

### Usage in HTML

```html
<div class="stagger-children">
  <div class="card animate-on-scroll">Service 1</div>
  <div class="card animate-on-scroll">Service 2</div>
  <div class="card animate-on-scroll">Service 3</div>
</div>

<ul class="stagger-children">
  <li class="animate-on-scroll">Skill 1</li>
  <li class="animate-on-scroll">Skill 2</li>
  <li class="animate-on-scroll">Skill 3</li>
</ul>
```

### Timing Considerations

- Delay increment: 0.1s (100ms) feels natural
- Max total stagger: ~0.5-0.6s (don't make user wait too long)
- For long lists (10+ items), cap the stagger

```css
/* Cap stagger for long lists */
.stagger-children > .animate-on-scroll:nth-child(n+7) {
  --stagger-delay: 0.6s; /* All items after 6th animate together */
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria

